{%- comment -%}
  Ganguram — Driving-distance config (Phase 2.11D; Routes API since 2.11I.1).

  Publishes window.GanguramDistanceConfig (outlet origin + API key + enable flag) and loads
  assets/ganguram-distance.js (window.GanguramDistance). Distances are computed via the
  **Routes API** (computeRouteMatrix, REST) on the merchant browser key — NOT the legacy
  Distance Matrix service. Used for FULL-ADDRESS selections (a confirmed distanceKm for the
  cart distance slabs) and the pincode-AREA estimate range (Phase 2.11I).

  FAIL-OPEN: no outlet origin / no key / Routes API failure -> no confirmed distance; the
  cart stays on the estimated pincode/zone path and the popup shows the configured fallback
  range. No checkout / shipping-charge / ShipZip / SBZ / zipLogic / resolver / settings_data
  change. The browser key must have the **Routes API** enabled (the store key already does).

  Origin is the outlet "lat,lng" from the theme setting `ganguram_outlet_origin`
  (Theme settings -> "Ganguram - Address search"). Enabled only when it is set.
{%- endcomment -%}
<script>
  window.GanguramDistanceConfig = {
    enabled: {% if settings.ganguram_outlet_origin != blank %}true{% else %}false{% endif %},
    origin: {{ settings.ganguram_outlet_origin | default: '' | json }},
    apiKey: {{ settings.google_maps_api_key | default: '' | strip_html | json }}
  };
</script>
<script src="{{ 'ganguram-distance.js' | asset_url }}" defer></script>
